msgctxt "talk17"
msgid ""
"<1.so>People usually say stuff like,<2.pa>\n"
"\"Isn't this more of a <3.se_co>sheep stable<4.re_co>\n"
"than a horse stable?\"\n"
"<5.so>I may be bad at raising horses,\n"
"but I can't help the fact that we've\n"
"had a lot of sheep births here!\n"
"<6.so>Who cares anyway? What's so wrong\n"
"about that?!\n"
"\n"
"...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<7.so>*ahem* <8.pa>I'm sorry.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"It seems I've done it again..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk18"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I really don't care if you start calling this\n"
"place the <2.se_co>Akkala Sheep Stable<3.re_co>. Really.\n"
"See. If. I. Care."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: set_colour (red)
#. 6: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk19"
msgid ""
"<1.so>They say he's the owner of something\n"
"called the <2.se_co>Fang and Bone<3.re_co>.<4.pa> It only\n"
"appears at <5.se_co>night<6.re_co>, or so they say."
msgstr ""

#. 1: text_size
#. 2: sound
#. 3: pause (longer)
#. 4: text_size
#. 5: sound
#. 6: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk20"
msgid ""
"<1.te_si><2.so>*inhale* <3.pa>*exhale*<4.te_si>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<5.so>Hi. I'm Kaifa.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"I'm the eldest daughter.<6.pa>\n"
"And..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk21"
msgid "<1.so>I'm...<2.pa>I'm sorry."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk22"
msgid "<1.so>Be careful out there."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk23"
msgid "<1.so>We should probably do that, too..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: set_colour (red)
#. 6: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk24"
msgid ""
"<1.so>It seems the <2.se_co>East Akkala Stable<3.re_co> up north<4.pa>\n"
"is hiring soldiers for protection because\n"
"of the rumors about <5.se_co>Kilton<6.re_co>."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk25"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Other than Father, it's just women here.<2.pa>\n"
"I don't feel as secure as I'd like to..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk26"
msgid "<1.so>Do you need anything else?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

